    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 158.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State.</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 12, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> It will be proper for you to inform Mr.
                            Thouvenel that I have communicated the substance of his explanations
                            given to you on the subject of Mexican complications to Mr. Romero,
                            excluding, however, all that part of the explanations which was stated
                            to you by Mr. Thouvenel to be confidential. A copy of my communication
                            to Mr. Romero is annexed.</p>
                <p>The frankness and distinctness which we have maintained throughout with
                            all parties on this grave subject have seemed to require this
                            proceeding.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
